I asked Claude.ai and ChatGPT to each build a website for:

Design the most exciting and romantic Canada Day itineraries in Metro Vancouv=
er for Eric and his girlfriend Jung, for Wednesday July 1, 2026. The couple l=
ives in Vancouver and loves food, arts, live music, dance and movement, the o=
utdoors, and scenic waterfront moments.

YOUR JOB: propose FIVE distinct full-day itineraries, each built around a dif=
ferent MOOD/THEME, then name your single top recommendation for this couple. =
Give each itinerary an evocative name and a clear morning -> afternoon -> eve=
ning flow with specific stops, rough times, realistic travel between them, an=
d a fireworks or sunset finale where it fits. Be concrete, opinionated, and d=
ecisive.

Use these REAL, verified July 1, 2026 events (all free unless noted):
- Canada Together @ Canada Place, downtown waterfront, 11am-6pm - the biggest=
 July 1 party outside Ottawa (40th anniversary): multiple live-music stages (=
headliner The Strumbellas), Indigenous marketplace, citizenship ceremony, foo=
d trucks.
- Steveston Salmon Festival, Richmond - street parade 10am-noon, the famous s=
almon BBQ bake, Barney Bentall on the main stage; classic small-town patrioti=
c energy.
- Granville Island, False Creek - public market opens ~7:30am, False Creek "w=
ater ballet" 8:30am, giant cake-cutting noon, lobster boil, PLUS free / pay-w=
hat-you-can TD Vancouver International Jazz Festival sets on the island. Comp=
act, walkable foodie + arts + waterfront in one spot.
- Grouse Mountain, North Vancouver - 9am-9pm (ticketed Skyride; wearing a tea=
m jersey =3D 15% off), Lumberjack Show, birds-of-prey demo, live music, panor=
amic city + ocean views.
- North Van Shipyards, Lonsdale waterfront - live music, splash park, beer ga=
rden, and Canadian Navy ships docked at the pier.
- Bard on the Beach, Vanier Park (Kitsilano) - Shakespeare under an open-back=
ed tent with the mountains and English Bay behind the stage at sunset (ticket=
ed); the most romantic culture pick.
- Capilano Suspension Bridge, North Vancouver - treetop walkways and cliffwal=
k (ticketed; a FREE Canada Day shuttle runs from downtown, and a BC-resident =
ticket converts to a year pass).
- VanDusen Botanical Garden + Bloedel Conservatory / Queen Elizabeth Park - q=
uiet scenic gardens plus a city-view summit; a calm romantic counterpoint to =
the crowds.
- Stanley Park Seawall, beaches, and English Bay - free cycling, picnics, and=
 sunset.
- Junction Public Market, Granville Square downtown - local artisans and a li=
censed waterfront patio 11am-7pm.
- Harbour Cruises sunset dinner cruise from Coal Harbour (ticketed) - buffet =
+ live music gliding past Canada Place and the North Shore mountains.

FIREWORKS - IMPORTANT: there are NO fireworks inside the City of Vancouver th=
is year. Every finale is in a suburb at about 10:15pm: Surrey (paired with a =
Josh Ross concert), Burnaby Central Park (StreetFest, the most central, easy =
by SkyTrain), White Rock beach and pier (the most romantic, bursting over the=
 water at sunset), and Coquitlam / Port Coquitlam (April Wine at Castle Park)=
. Plan the finale accordingly.

Themes to draw from across the five itineraries: (a) big patriotic spectacle,=
 (b) foodie / culinary crawl, (c) arts & culture, (d) outdoors & nature / act=
ive, (e) romantic & scenic / low-key, (f) live-music & festival energy - pick=
 the five strongest for a couple.

Caveats to respect: July 1 is a Wednesday and the FIFA World Cup is running c=
oncurrently (watch parties everywhere; some suburban parades are "stationary"=
 this year), so build realistic travel time between stops, avoid over-packing=
 the day, and flag anything ticketed or that needs advance booking.

